django-assume
Copyright Full Factor Technologies Inc.

django-assume is a reusable Django app that allows assuming user accounts using
a custom button in admin on the change user form.

Installation:

1.  Add assume to settings.INSTALLED_APPS

2.  Add one of the custom authentication backends in assume.backends to
    settings.AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS, e.g.:

        AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS = (
            'assume.backends.AssumableModelBackend',
            'django.contrib.auth.backends.ModelBackend',
        )

3.  Include assume.admin_urls in the project's urls:

        urlpatterns += patterns('',
            (r'^admin/', include('assume.admin_urls')),
        )

    or add a specific pattern to specify the next url to be redirected to
    after a user has been assumed:

        urlpatterns += patterns('',
            url(
                r'^admin/auth/user/(\d+)/assume/$',
                'assume.views.assume_user',
                {'next_url': '/demo'},
                name = 'assume_user'
            ),
        )
